(firstQuint)Evaluation of the Effectiveness, Safety, and Tolerability of Duac Akne Gel and Epiduo Gel in the Treatment of Facial Acne Vulgaris.

 Multiple physiopathological factors have been associated with acne vulgaris.

 Drug combinations are frequently used to address these factors and to improve efficacy in the treatment of acne.

 The current study proposes to compare a fixed-dose (once-daily) combination gel product containing benzoyl peroxide (BPO)and clindamycin against a fixed-dose (once-daily) combination gel product containing BPO and adapalene for the treatment of facial acne vulgaris.

